For 8 people
Preparation Time: 15 minutes
Cooking Time: 20 minutes

Ingredients
500g lamb mince
1 large onion, finely chopped
1/2 cup parsley, finely chopped
1/4 cup coriander
1 tablespoon ground cumin
1 tablespoon tomato paste
1/2 cup breadcrumbs
1 egg
salt and pepper, to taste
1/2 cup flour
2 tablespoons olive oil


Step  1: Thoroughly mix together mince, onion, parsley, coriander,cumin, tomato paste, breadcrumbs, egg, and salt and pepper in a large bowl. 
Step  2: Prepare a tray with plastic wrap.
Step  3: Prepare the mixture into 16 ball shaped portions, then lay them evenly onto the tray.
Step  4: Cover over tray + portions with more plastic wrap. 
Step  5: Allow to cool in fridge for 10-15 mins.
Step  6: Once cooled, remove from fridge, and heat up a moderate sized pan on medium heat.
Step  7: Cover koftas in flour. 
Step  8: Place a tablespoon of oil and half the koftas(use less if using smaller pan) in the pan. 
Step  9: Tend to and turn the koftas for 12-15 minutes or until cooked through. 
Step 10: Remove koftas and place them on a plate/tray lined with paper towels, to absorb the oil.
Step 11: Repeat cooking process with remaining koftas, cleaning out and replacing oil between batches.
Step 12: Serve.


